result.name: Sichuan House

reviews.text: Loved the food. We were 4 adults and 4 children. We started with very few skewers since we knew the mains was going to be a lot. We ordered okra wrapped in bacon which although it looked undercooked, turned out to be very tasty. We also ordered squid and eel skewers. Both of which were tasty. As our mains we ordered a medium bowl of soup which we shared amongst us. The spice range ranges from 1-5. We opted for 2 since we are Indians and can take quite a bit of spice. And yet we found 2 quite spicy. My husband accidentally got some spicy soup into his eye while slurping the noodles. It was a painful experience and he had to get it washed out. So be careful! Overall, the staff are warm and friendly as well. Constantly coming over to make sure we had everything we needed. They replaced chop sticks that we dropped (try managing all this with 4 very fidgety children) even before we realised we had dropped a chop stick. Very good service.
Best time to go at 11:00 before noon. A salad bar and a main course at HK$ 100. Try it yourself.
Authentic Sichuan food. Young Master beers on tap. Delicious!

Favourite Sichuan restaurant with amazing variety of dishes. This Yoho branch, is probably the best in Hong Kong so far. Ambience and service is very good here. The fish is chilli oil with an upgrade to the mandarin fish is highly recommended. Chili Prawns are fiery enough to steam your ears. The fruit iced tea is fantastic.
Good spicy food...

閒日下午茶抵食$38起加一，包三款冷盆，一份熱食及冷飲品，免茶，選擇多! 食物有水準。
